snippet.textDisplay:
It's been long, I'm following all the Coke Studio episodes from season 1 till now. I can be wrong, but it seems like Coke Studio Season 9 isn't to its earlier seasons. Guess Rohail Hayat was a far better producer and arranger. Earlier seasons were full of very talented musicians and vocals/singers, this season I can hardly find some unique vocal texture, mostly excessive use of instrument are killing the wonderful vocals and composition.

 I guess Coke Studio should consider that, its productions are not about making different kind of remixes with heavy use of instruments, rather it's supposed to be the wonderful combination of vocals and musicians magic. Coke Studio Season 1 to 6 are perfect example. 

Anyway, didn't mean to hurt anyone by saying all these things. I know all the singers and musicians are very talented. Probably they're not having their chances to show their own flavor. Thanking you all behind the production.
